Loop certified driver on stdin for persistent benchmark protocol.

Rewrap the Haskell entry point `Main_Certified.hs` so that one
invocation of the resulting `svp_certified` binary handles many bench
requests, instead of spawning a fresh process per call. Each line of
stdin is one matrix in `[[Integer]]` Haskell-read syntax; each line of
stdout is the squared norm emitted by `test_certified`. The binary exits
cleanly on EOF.

This mirrors `01-persistent-stdin.patch` for the native Isabelle LLL
driver. The certified path additionally shells out to the `fplll` binary
inside `test_certified`, so the persistent protocol amortizes only the
Haskell driver startup and not the per-request external reducer process.

--- a/haskell_sources/Main_Certified.hs
+++ b/haskell_sources/Main_Certified.hs
@@ -1,11 +1,15 @@
 {-# LANGUAGE LambdaCase #-}
 module Main(main)
   where
-import System.Environment
+import System.IO
 import LLL_SVP

-main = do
-  as <- getArgs
-  input <- readFile (as !! 0)
-  let mat = (read input :: [[Integer]])
-  putStrLn (show (test_certified mat))
+main = do
+  hSetBuffering stdout LineBuffering
+  contents <- getContents
+  mapM_ runOne (lines contents)
+  where
+    runOne line = do
+      let mat = (read line :: [[Integer]])
+      putStrLn (show (test_certified mat))
+      hFlush stdout
